snippet.title: Stranger Things 5 | Official Teaser | Netflix
snippet.description:
Every battle has led to this.

More about Stranger Things 5:
The fall of 1987. Hawkins is scarred by the opening of the Rifts, and our heroes are united by a single goal: find and kill Vecna. But he has vanished ‚Äî his whereabouts and plans unknown. Complicating their mission, the government has placed the town under military quarantine and intensified its hunt for Eleven, forcing her back into hiding. As the anniversary of Will‚Äôs disappearance approaches, so does a heavy, familiar dread. The final battle is looming ‚Äî and with it, a darkness more powerful and more deadly than anything they‚Äôve faced before. To end this nightmare, they‚Äôll need everyone ‚Äî the full party ‚Äî standing together, one last time.

Watch on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/title/81297917

Netflix is one of the world's leading entertainment services, with over 300 million paid memberships in over 190 countries enjoying TV series, films and games across a wide variety of genres and languages. Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films‚Äô Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story‚Ä¶and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question‚Ä¶do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films‚Äô Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story‚Ä¶and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question‚Ä¶do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

snippet.title: "Malai Thacha" Sabin Rai & The Pharaoh
snippet.description:
We're back with a fresh new song " Malai Thacha" . It's a modern rock sound filled with driving guitars, tight grooves and powerful vocals. It's a style that pushes us into new territory while keeping the raw, live feel of a real band playing together. 
We wanted to create something that hits hard on stage and connects with every listener, from passionate  music lovers to young musicians looking for inspiration. If you love rock that feels alive, this one's for you !.

Sabin Rai & The Pharaoh :
Sabin Rai - Vocals
Binod Lama - Drums
Jeevan lama - Bass
John Shrestha - Guitar
Steven Tamang - Audio Engineer
Subash Gurung - Audio Engineer
Jitesh Shakya - Stage manager
Abiz Basukala - Live Visuals.
Narayan Khatri - Light Engineer.

Music | Composition | Arrangement : Sabin Rai & The Pharaoh.
Recording Studio - The Project Studio .
Recording engineer - Binay Amataya.
Mix/ Master/Audio Production - Steven Tamang.
English Subtitles : Maha Pralaya

snippet.title: Shiv Tandav Stotram | Shankar Mahadevan | ‡§∞‡§æ‡§µ‡§£ ‡§∞‡§ö‡§ø‡§§ ‡§∂‡§ø‡§µ ‡§§‡§æ‡§Ç‡§°‡§µ ‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡•ã‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ | Shiv Stuti | Shiv Stotra
snippet.description:
'Shiv Tandav Stotram', (traditionally written by 'Ravana') sung by Shankar Mahadevan. 

Shiva Tandava Stotram is a powerful hymn in Sanskrit, composed by Ravana, praising Lord Shiva and his cosmic dance of destruction and creation. It vividly describes Shiva's divine form, attributes, and the energetic dance that symbolizes both destruction and recreation. Reciting this stotram is believed to bring spiritual benefits, including liberation from worldly bonds and a connection with Shiva's divine energy. 

#ShivTandav #Shiva #Tandava #Hinduism #Sanskrit #Stotram #Mantras #Chanting #Devotion #Meditation #Ravana #Mythology #Spirituality #CosmicDance #LordShiva #BenefitsOfShivTandav #SpiritualHymn #SacredText #DivineDance #HinduGod #HinduDeity #IndianCulture #SpiritualAwakening #PositiveEnergy #InnerPeace #SpiritualGrowth #Protection #Strength #Blessings #Purification #Liberation #TandavaStotram #ShivaTandavaStotram #ShivaTandavaStrotam

Title - Shiv Tandav Stotram
Singer - Shankar Mahadevan
Composer - Uma Mohan, Shailesh Dani
Lyrics - Traditional
Language - Sanskrit

Production House Squaredeal Productions
Ai Supervisor - Ashiya pal 
Ai Editor - Siddharth Tiwari

                               Lyrics
Jata tavi galajjala pravaha pavitasthale
Galea valambya lambitam bhujanga tungamalikam ||
Damad damad damad dama ninada vadda marvayam
Chakara chand tandavam tanotu nah shivah shivam ||1|| 

Jata kata hasam bhrama bhrama nilimpa nirjhari
Vilolavi chivalarai viraja mana murdhani ||
Dhagadhagadha gajjvala lalata patta pavake
Kishora chandra shekhare ratih pratikshanam mama ||2|| 

Dhara dharendra nandini vilasa bandhu bandhura
Sphuradi ganta santati pramoda mana manase ||
Krupa kataksha dhorani nirudhadurdha rapadi
Kvachit digambare mano vinodametu vastuni ||3||

Jata bhujanga pingala sphurat phana mani prabha
Kadamba kunkuma drava pralipta digva dhumukhe ||
Madandha sindhura sphura tvaguttari ya medure
Mano vinoda madbhutam bibhartu bhuta bhartari ||4||

Sahasra lochana prabhritya shesha lekha shekhara
Prasuna dhulidhorani vidhu saranghri pithabhuh ||
Bhujanga raja malaya nibaddha jata jutaka
Shriyai chiraya jayatam chakora bandhu shekharah ||5||

Lalata chatva rajvala dhanajn jaya sphu lingabha
Nipita pancha sayakam naman nilimpa nayakam ||
Sudha mayukha lekhaya viraja mana shekharam
Maha kapali sampade shiro jata lamastu nah ||6||

Karala bhala pattika dhagad dhagad dhagaj jvaltt
Ddhanajn jaya huti kruta prachanda pancha sayake ||
Dhara dharendra nandini kuchagra chitra patraka
Prakalpa naika shilpini trilochane ratir mama ||7||

Navina megha mandali niruddha durdha rasphurat
Kuhunishithi nitamah prabandha baddha kandharah ||
Nilimpa nirjhari dhara stanotu krutti sindhurah
Kala nidhana bandhurah shriyam jagad dhurandharah ||8||

Prafulla nila pankaja prapancha kali maprabha
Valambi kantha kandali ruchi prabaddha kandharam ||
Smarachchhidam purachchhidam bhavachchhidam makhachchhidam
Gajachchhidandha kachhidam tamanta kachchhidam bhaje ||9||

Akharva sarva mangala kala kadamba manjari
Rasa pravaha madhuri vijrum bhanama dhuvratam ||
Smarantakam purantakam bhavantakam makhantakam
Gajanta kandha kantakam tamanta kantakam bhaje ||10||

Jayatvada bhravibhrama bhramad bhujanga mashvasa
Dvi nirgamatkrama sphurat karala bhala havyavat ||
Dhimid dhimid dhimidhvanan mrudanga tunga mangala
Dhvani karma pravartita prachanda tandavah shivah ||11||

Shrushadvi chitra talpayor bhujanga maukti kasrajo
Garishtha ratna loshthayoh suhrudvi paksha pakshayoh ||
Trunara vinda chakshushoh praja mahi mahendrayoh
Sama pravrutikah samam pravartayan manah 
kada sada shivam bhajamyaham ||12||

Kada nilimpa nirjhari nikunja kotare vasanh
Vimukta durmatihs sada shirah stha manjalim vahan ||
Vimukta lola lochano lalama bhala lagnakah
Shiveti mantra muncharan sada sukhi bhavamyaham ||13||

Idam hi nityameva mukta mukta mottamam stavam
Pathan smaran bruvannaro vishuddhi meti santatam ||
Hare gurav subhakti mashu yati nanyatha gatim
Vimohanam hi dehinam sushankarasya chintanam ||14||

localized.description:
'Shiv Tandav Stotram', (traditionally written by 'Ravana') sung by Shankar Mahadevan. 

Shiva Tandava Stotram is a powerful hymn in Sanskrit, composed by Ravana, praising Lord Shiva and his cosmic dance of destruction and creation. It vividly describes Shiva's divine form, attributes, and the energetic dance that symbolizes both destruction and recreation. Reciting this stotram is believed to bring spiritual benefits, including liberation from worldly bonds and a connection with Shiva's divine energy.

Presenting Affair ‚Äî the captivating new love song from the movie Maalik!
Starring Rajkummar Rao and Manushi Chhillar, Affair is a passionate tale of love, desire, and secret emotions. With dynamic vocals by Khesari Lal Yadav, Shradha Mishra, and Sachin-Jigar, the song is elevated by the soulful composition of Sachin-Jigar and heartfelt lyrics by Amitabh Bhattacharya.

snippet.title: Every PUBG Mobile Team You Need to Know for EWC 2025 : The Ultimate Guide
snippet.description:
PMWC 2025 is coming soon. And as an Indian, I know most of you don‚Äôt know who half these EWC teams are. And that‚Äôs completely okay‚Ä¶ because we have been away from the international circuit. 

But after you watch this video‚Ä¶ you‚Äôll know everything you need to know about these teams and watching EWC will be so much more fun.

I basically went crazy for the past few weeks. Watched every interview I could find, stalked roster announcements, got way too invested in Twitter drama between players... all so I could explain why this tournament is actually insane.
Here's what I figured out:

1. Top teams and why they matter
2. Three teams that could absolutely wreck everyone's predictions
3. The players who are straight-up built different
4. Some spicy takes that might age terribly (we'll see üòÖ)
5. Where does India‚Äôs Team Aryan stand right now and what do I expect of them?  

I'm breaking down a lot of teams and honestly, by the end of this you'll find the team you're actually rooting for.

This isn't me trying to sound smart or predict everything perfectly. It's just‚Ä¶ these storylines are too good not to share. And as an Indian, I know we have been away from the global scene for a while now‚Ä¶ so it‚Äôs important to go informed.

Fair warning: If teams I get excited about don‚Äôt even qualify for finals, that's just PUBG being PUBG. I‚Äôm just someone who loves gaming‚Ä¶ not a fortune teller. So ‚ÄòPanoti‚Äô mat bolna üòÇüò°

üëá Seriously though‚Ä¶  drop a comment and tell me which team caught your attention. Any players you're curious about?



~

My Instagram:
https://www.instagram.com/its.ayush.gg/

~

Thanks for watching and supporting the journey to become India's Best Gaming Creator! :)
